927  a(OCoLC)oca05357877  aDLCbengerdacDLCdNNU  s1971t1974?2edtf2 aFood (Restaurant : New York, N.Y.)  eSoHo (New York, N.Y.)2naf1 wriFounder:aGirouard, Tina1 wriFounder:aMatta-Clark, Gordon,d1943-19781 wriFounder:aHarris, Suzanne  aURIs added to this record for the PCC URI MARC Pilot. Please do not remove or edit the URIs.  aFood, c1999:bt.p. (Food) p. 27 (opened Sept. 25, 1971 at 127 Prince Str., an artist-run restaurant)  aNew York times, Apr. 30, 2020:bin an obituary on page B14 (Tina Girouard; born Cynthia Marie Girouard May 26, 1946 in DeQuincy, La., died Apr. 21 in Cecilia, La, aged 73; a risk-taking artist from rural Louisiana who played a catalytic role in the 1970s SoHo art scene in New York, helping to found the experimental gallery 112 Greene Street and the artist-run restaurant Food; Ms. Girouard joined forces with Mr. [Gordon] Matta-Clark, Caroline Gooden and Suzanne Harris to found the restaurant Food in 1971 at Prince and Wooster Streets; the [restaurant] space lasted not quite three years in its original incarnation, done in partly by its determination to avoid conventionality at all costs)00656nz  a2200157n  4500001001300000003000400013005001700017008004100034010001700075040001800092130003900110410008800149643002300237667014700260670009100407n  00010194 DLC20000406113654.0000406n| acacaaban          |a ana        an  00010194   aDLCbengcDLC 0aWildlife Conservation Society book2 aWildlife Conservation Society (New York, N.Y.).tWildlife Conservation Society book  aNew YorkbF. Watts  aGive as a quoted note if Wildlife Conservation Society is not recorded in the publication, distribution, etc. area of the bibliographic record  aA polar bear biologist at work, 2001:bCIP t.p. (A Wildlife Conservation Society book)03017cz  a2200409n  n  00010232 DLC20231004064550.0000412n| azannaabn          |a aaa        an  00010232 7 a578408692viaf1http://viaf.org/viaf/57840869  a(OCoLC)oca05197228  aDLCbengerdacDLCdDLCdWaU  f19632edtf1 aRockwell, David L.,d1963-  cAmericans2lcdgt  dDr.  cUnited StatesfAlbany (N.Y.)fMinneapolis (Minn.)fToronto (Ont.)fFairfax (Va.)2naf  aMilitary electronics industryaAeronautics, MilitaryaEnvironmental monitoring--Remote sensing2lcsh  aTeal Group Corp.2nafs1995  aGeorge Mason University2nafs2019  aUniversity of Mary Washington.2nafs2019t2020  aGeographersaMilitary historiansaUniversity and college faculty membersaPeriodical editors2lcdgt  aCollege teachers2lcsh  aAnalysts  aeng  qDavid Leon1 aRockwell, David,d1963-1 wnneaRockwell, David L.,cDr.2 wriGraduate of:aState University of New York at Albany2 wriGraduate of:aUniversity of Minnesota2 wriGraduate of:aUniversity of Toronto  aFormerly on undifferentiated name record: n  82054237  aJane's how to fly and fight in the F-14 Tomcat, c1999:bt.p. (Dr. David L. Rockwell) p. 3 of cover (aviation analyst with the Teal Group in Washington, D.C.)  aTeal Group website, September 29, 2023:babout > analysts  (Dr. David L. Rockwell, Director, Defense Electronics, has been at Teal Group since 1995, where he is editor of Teal's Military Electronics Briefing (MEB) as well as co-author of Teal's annual World Military Unmanned Aerial Systems: Market Profile and Forecast. Between 1990 and 1995, Dr. Rockwell was an NSERC (National Science and Engineering Research Council) Project Leader at the University of Toronto, conducting research focusing on remotely sensed topographical analysis. He earned his Ph.D. and M.A. in Geography, and an M.A. and B.A. in Military History; in 2019, Dr. Rockwell will be teaching at the University of Mary Washington near Washington, D.C.)  aResearchGate website, September 29, 2023:bprofile (David L. Rockwell, George Mason University Department of Geography and Geoinformation Science; Ph.D., University of Toronto.  Affiliations: August 2019- George Mason University ; August 20